< Review>
Highly recommend the Spicy Char Siu Ramen: the broth has great flavor with neither less nor more salty and spicy level to let you finish all the soup without drinking water; char siu(pork) is also very tasty.

Another must-have is Taiwanese Simmered Combo plate. This is the very classic Taiwanese style appetizer, though the price is a little bit too expensive.

It is still in soft opening mode and you cannot order any fried item, but they do offer decent service. Definitely will come back again!<//Review>

<Rate>4<//Rate><review>New Taiwanese ramen place! In soft opening right now so have limited menu offering, and also cash only until their machines are set up.

We tried both the spicy and non-spicy ramen. The broth is decent, the soft-boiled egg is excellent, the chashu meat tastes good but a little thin. It didn't actually quite taste like ramen because the noodles are thin and soft. It tasted more like a Chinese noodle dish.

We also ordered the stewed combo plate. They didn't have seaweed so we asked for extra pork blood rice cake. The pork blood rice cake was really good, tofu was good, and the pork ears were a little too crunchy for our liking.

Service was good and friendly, we got our food pretty fast after ordering. Overall have some room for improvement, but we will definitely return to try some of their other dishes once available!<//review>< pictures>

< Text>
It's soft opening so they only serve spicy/non-spicy char siu ramen, cold noodles and Taiwanese simmered combo plate. I like the combo plate a lot. It includes pig ear, pork blood rice cake, pressed bean curd and seaweed. Their spicy ramen broth was ok and not that spicy. Char siu was seared and really tender. Onsen egg was unfortunately not marinated. There were also nori, corns, bamboo shoots and green onions. Overall I like it and would come back for more dishes.<//Text>

Fairly new and under the radar, this place serves pretty good ramen. The place is awesomely decorated with Star Wars posters everywhere. I've tried their spicy signature ramen and Garlic ramen. Both are excellent. The broth is thick, creamy, and flavorful. The noodles are on the thicker side. Love the takoyaki! It's so soft and fluffy. Staff is really friendly and nice. There's no line, because I don't think people know it exists. So if you're looking to try a new ramen place, I recommend coming here. I don't think you'll regret it.< /text>

<name>shekhar paudel<//name><Rating>5< /Rating><Text>This review is based on my car buying experience at MDK International in February of 2020.

MDK International is a car dealership that we wish all car dealerships were like.
I recommend this place to all of my friends and family. I even wish more used car dealerships would adopt their method and culture because the whole process with them is simple, efficient and most importantly what I think is honest.

They had detailed information of their inventory online and responded to all my phone calls and emails. When I was ready to see the car, I made an appointment online, showed up at the dealership and the car was ready for inspection. This has not always been the case with most other used car dealerships. The car was exactly as pictured and described on their website. When I was ready to buy the car, the owner and staff at MDK went beyond what I consider to be their duty to help me with the paperwork.

The absolute best thing about this place is the fact that it is a no-haggle dealership with what is unquestionably a fair price tag. You would have to be an experienced negotiator and car buyer with mechanical knowledge to be able to negotiate down the price tag at other dealerships to the levels offered by MDK. Not everyone has such skills, time, or even the will to negotiate with most car dealerships. We all know buying used cars from most dealerships is one of the worst buying experiences in our lives. We are never sure if we are paying hundreds or most likely thousands more because the dealership is out to make as much profit as possible with every person and every transaction. I know that most people would rather buy a new car by paying twice the amount of a used car and sleep well knowing they are getting exactly what they paid for. For those who want to rest easy knowing they are getting exactly what they paid for, and that they paid exactly what an expert negotiator would pay for with days of work in another dealership without a fixed price, this is the place to buy your used car.

I am very satisfied with my car buying process with MDK International. I think what MDK have created is exactly what we as consumers imagine an ideal car dealership ought to be.

I am not reviewing the car itself because MDK doesn't manufacture them. However, I am very happy with the car I bought from them.</Text>< Resp>

<rate>5</rate><Text>Integrity!
After researching MDK for a few months, I went to check out a few cars for a test drive and to get a feel for this dealer.
Everyone I encountered was courteous, helpful, and knowledgeable meaning they knew car features by year, upgrades, engine differences etc.

I tested one of the sales people by asking if he could "recommend" a mechanic for me to inspect a vehicle I wanted to buy. He twice said he could not as it would be a conflict of interest. I appreciated that.

They have a strong eclectic selection of cars and their prices are very competitive to major dealers and smaller independents. I will be buying my next car from MDK once I decide on the model I like.
Very pleasant experience and will recommend.< /Text>< Pics>

If you can spend a little bit more, buy a newer car or if you know how to source parts on-line and have a good independent mechanic to install these parts these cars have great value and very fun to own without spending too much. If you are looking to buy 10 y/o European car with higher miles please expect to spend something on service or just buy a newer one. There is a reason why manufactures only offer 4 yr/50K mile warranties on these cars. If you can spend a little bit more, buy a newer car or if you know how to source parts on-line and have a good independent mechanic to install these parts these cars have great value and very fun to own without spending too much. This particular Audi A4 Convertible is still for sale and in great shape for it's year and miles without usual Audi problems - vacuum pump is not leaking, valve-cover gasket is not leaking, rear window and top in great shape, and no common interior issues, and no PCV / Turbo issues. If you know these cars you probably know that everything else is just a sign of it's age. Thank you for taking your time reading this response."}</response>

< review>
*** Insider Information ***

I had worked for Mike and Darya for about 2 years. In that time, I'd come to deeply respect their work, and the way they do business.  I got into the car business because I love cars and motor vehicles, having built, restored, and modified many cars and hotrods over the years.

Mike is an excellent and ethical business person, and knows even more about cars than I do.  I have seen, firsthand, how he buys cars, and how he takes care of them. I've bought stuff from Mike, and I have brought family members and friends to buy cars from them, and every single one has been happy.

Mike and Darya are exceedingly fair people and some of their unique business practices reflect their no-nonsense approach to providing some of the best cars available. Believe it or not, but some customers are actually awful people who try to cheat good businesses out of whatever they can. I have seen this personally. Respect the small protections requested by simple rules like "No Joyrides".

*Some advice to make your transaction smoother* -- Make and keep your appointment. -- Research the car you want so that you know the market (you're probably getting a great deal, but's good to know that before you go in) -- If you're trading in a car, research that too, and expect a fair offer (they don't play games) -- Bring in your ID, license, proof of insurance, and any necessary documents if you're financing (proof of income, residence, etc.) -- If you're trading in a car, bring the title and any other documents -- Even the simplest car transaction can take some time to organize the substantial paperwork for a bank, and/or the DMV, allow time for this and be cool.

Why am I reviewing a former employer? Because I've also been a customer, and they're good people who run a good business. We need more of that in the world. Cheers!</review>

< Review>
About 10 months ago I had to make one of the biggest hardest to decide decisions of my life... I needed complete dentures, and at the age of 82 I really didn't know if I was ready to make a huge commitment like that.... Pain????  money???? permanent relief and ability to eat normally ??? <rating>1<//rating>< Date>
1490502384911</Date>
<Pictures>None</Pictures><text>DO NOT USE DOCTOR SLAUGHTER. I AM STILL SUFFERING FROM HIS MISTAKE.

I got my wisdom teeth extracted by Doctor Slaughter in late July of summer 2016. It is now March 2017, and I just had my second surgery to fix things that could have avoided in the first place if he did the surgery right. A week after I had my wisdom teeth taken out, I got an infection so I was put on a small dose of antibiotic by Slaughter. A week or so later I had finished the antibiotic and left the country for a vacation. My first night in Belize, I woke up and the infection had gotten very bad. That morning I went to a doctor in the nearest town and he had to squeeze the infection out with his hands because it was so bad. He then put me on a stronger antibiotic (what Slaughter should have put me on in the first place) and it killed most of the infection. When I got back home, I went back to Slaughter and he found a piece of dead bone that he left in. He thought nothing of it.

Fast forward to 8 months later and I am still having severe pain. I went into an oral surgeons office a couple weeks ago and he said from the looks of it, there was still an infection. Yesterday, March 24th I had a biopsy and they found a piece of root from my wisdom tooth that had been left in there!!! It was causing a serious infection to where my bone was very soft and mushy.

3 surgeries when this could have been avoided if done correctly. Doctor Slaughter is definitely not a good option if you are looking for an oral surgeon.<//text></record></dataset><record>

<date>1548225240680< /date><Gmap_id>0x80c2db2ad256cb1b:0x57dbee5fe1d672fc</Gmap_id>< userid>
101105929559731298820<//userid>
<rating>4<//rating>< text>
This northern Chinese style noodle house is a bit hidden in the plaza and a hole in the wall, but very  worth visiting.

We had the pickled Napa and lamb stew, pan fried pork buns, eggplant with baby shrimp, and baby cucumber fungus with egg. The sour from the pickled Napa countered the lamb really well and the sweetness of the egg went well with the oyster sauce in the cucumber dish. Each dish was great and distinct.< /text>

< Review>
The facility is generally clean, but if you're a person who needs access to your items alot this isn't the place for you. They close at 6 pm during the week and 5 pm on weekends, which is generally during normal peoples work hours. Also, if you need long term storage look into other options, I've experienced a 40% price increase in almost 2 years.</Review>

<Time>1413572479096</Time><rate>5< /rate>< Text>
I have never written a review for any guitar store that I have been too before. That needs rectifying. The casual atmosphere, knowledgeable 'family' of staff, and a very varied, constantly changing stock of guitars and amps makes a visit to Moze a must.

In the past couple of months I have bought a Trace Elliott Super Tramp (a real sleeper of an amp), a Vintage 'Peter Green' Les Paul copy and various accessories. The staff are usually willing to deal and prices are excellent for any guitar store let alone a small non-chain shop. This place feels much larger than it really is.

I will be back frequently for as long as I live in San Diego. I can't recommend this place more highly.< /Text>

<review>I called Fletcher Jones service as soon as I heard a little trouble with starting my ignition, and service advisor, Steve Bates, invited me to come on by. Within 30 minutes, I was driving away in what seemed to be a brand new GLA. The rentals are provided via Enterprise, and even those employees maintain the incomparable customer service that Fletcher Jones has been consistently providing throughout the 20+ years my family and I have been customers. From the advisors to the valet, cleaning service, coffee shop, etc, the employees I've come across there seem to have been trained very well in customer satisfaction, as most seem to reflect positive attitudes, urgency to fulfill customers' needs/requests, and seem to enjoy the work environment while maintaining the utmost professionalism. I've had cars from Crevier and Land Rover Newport Beach, and while they offer similar services (loaner cars, coffee, free car washes, etc), Fletcher Jones is in a league of its' own. Additionally, the complimentary airport shuttle service is extremely convenient, arriving within about 5-10 minutes upon notifying them of your arrival. Last time I dropped it off for a last minute weekend getaway, they were even able to squeeze in the service I needed, and, as always, got my car back sparkling clean.

<Name>mel blas</Name><date>1574524511659</date><Rate>5</Rate>< Review>
The Fletcher Jones experience of buying and servicing a Mercedes is unique. The size and scope of the operation is beyond anything approaching a normal auto dealership. It has it's wrinkles, but it's customer oriented philosophy has the resources to satisfy almost any issue. We have purchased several new Mercedes there, the most recent a 450 CLS. It's a beautiful car, but has a seat issue that makes driving it an uncomfortable experience. I brought the car to a local Mercedes dealer just after purchasing it, to see if anything could be done and they did their best, but there was no fix. They suggested to contact Mercedes and, of course it fell on deaf ears. I brought it to the attention of Eric Smith the Service Director and Fletcher Jones , on my initial service this week and he immediately recognized , the seat wasn't typical and said he would have the seat bottom opened to see if anything could be done. That evening Mike Asher, Service Adviser sent me pictures of the seat and it was obvious the seat lacked padding and although outside of the Mercedes design, they suggested  adding some padding. This fix was offered at no charge, but made sure , I understood it could not be undone. It's too early to see if it will work, but so far there is a definite improvement of comfort. On a side note, as a long time Mercedes owner, I wish CLS 450 owners would complain, as the front seat are not normal and of Mercedes quality..<//Review>
